    "body": "Eh. I'm actually kinda ok with the way it turned out. If it's non-pub it shouldn't wind up in the object file as a public symbol (if it does, we're doing-stuff-wrong in codegen) and we can potentially just mark it as a throw-me-away sort of value harder if LLVM requires further convincing.\n\nConsidering that static asserts in C are typically done by composing a negative-sized array and allowing the compiler to yell about that, I consider this implementation already pretty luxurious :)\n",
